@dagar FYI
Seems like tailsitter mission and position control is broken on master (it does not track at all, roll setpoints changes sign frequently).
I found a working version not too long ago and will do a bisect.

This isn't the ideal solution, but for the majority of cases (good boards and bad) it will bring all sensors back (hard reset and reboot commanded).

Tested on several different pixhawks (3dr, hobbyking, etc).

@svpcom could you try this?

@priseborough Since I can't push to your branch I opened a new PR with my changes.
Main thing I changed is that if the airspeed sensor is activated, connected but "broken" (e.g. pitot full of dirt or e.g. user forgets to remove a pitot calibration cover) we will start fusing beta 3 seconds after forward transition.

On a sidenote, we now have two ways of deactivating the airspeed fusion, FW_ARSP_MODE and EKF2_ARSP_THR, we should probably clean that up at some point

Initial fix created in response to https://github.com/PX4/ecl/issues/399

This prevents a condition where depending on the method of entering into fixed wing flight, it is possible for sideslip fusion to commence before airspeed fusion. This can lead to bad wind estimates and rejection of airspeed measurements. This patch ensures that in where airspeed sensing is being used, sideslip fusion will not be requested until wind estimation has started.

